000000008d9dc510f23c2657fc4f67bea30078cc.note: It's known that Satoshi sent BTC to Hal in #170 and this block's coinbase is the output spent there.

Patoshi.note: The miner known as Patoshi is a placeholder for a hypothesized early miner identified by statistical analysis of early mining activity. While some believe Patoshi and Satoshi Nakamoto to be one and the same, others disagree. Since early miner data is very sparse, Patoshi-mined blocks are included for their curiosity value. Interested users can decide for themselves about the validitiy of the Patoshi analysis by reading the content at satoshiblocks.info.

Satoshi.note: The attribution of this block to Satoshi is dependent on archived email communication shared by Mike Hearn, the eventual recipient of BTC mined in this block.
